text:
💡 What are conditionals?
Conditionals let us run different code depending on whether something is True or False.
if weight &gt; 1000:
    print("Big hippo!")
The structure:
if condition:
    do_this
elif another_condition:
    do_that
else:
    do_something_else


Code
weight = 1200

if weight &gt; 1000:
    print("Big hippo!")
else:
    print("Small hippo!")

🔄 if…elif…else chain
bmi = 32

if bmi &lt; 18.5:
    print("Underweight")
elif bmi &lt; 25:
    print("Normal weight")
elif bmi &lt; 30:
    print("Overweight")
else:
    print("Obese")


Code
